fields.name: fillLevel
fields.description: Current buffer fill level, i.e. number of epochs currently stored

fields.name: dropsAll
fields.description: Number of dropped epochs since startup

fields.name: dropsSinceMon
fields.description: Number of dropped epochs since last MON-BATCH message

fields.name: nextMsgCnt
fields.description: The next retrieved UBX-LOG-BATCH will have this msgCnt value

issues: Uses 'reserved1' for the first reserved field where others use 'reserved0'. This is a minor naming difference likely found in the specific document version.

adjudication.reasoning: All three extractions define an identical binary structure (length 12, identical field offsets and data types). The differences are cosmetic: Extraction 2 names the reserved field 'reserved1' while others use 'reserved0', and descriptions in Extractions 2 and 3 include usage notes absent in Extraction 1. The structural definition is consistent across M8, M9, and M10 generations.
